Always read code first before making changes.
Ask for review before implementing changes.
Run npm lint before completing changes.

Project Structure:
/apps/web - Next.js frontend
/apps/api - Backend service
/packages - Shared code
/content - Documentation
/supabase - Database config

Key Technologies:

- Next.js + React + TypeScript
- Turborepo (monorepo)
- Supabase (backend)
- Shadcn/UI + Tailwind
- PostHog + Resend

Critical Patterns:

- Server-side rendering compatible components
- Dark theme default (system disabled)
- Readonly<T> for props, React.ReactNode for children
- Strict TypeScript, no any
- Environment variables in turbo.json globalEnv
- Geist fonts + shadcn/ui + cn utility
- Shared code goes in packages/\*

Remember:

- Test both web and api
- Follow existing patterns
- Consider monorepo-wide impacts
